<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4515&amp;p=39281#p39281</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4515&amp;p=39281#p39281"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[USB Controller]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4515&amp;p=39281#p39281"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />And sorry tepples, but the first sentence of that post means nothing to me.  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><br /></div><br />A lot of cross-platform games are developed using a library such as Allegro, SDL, or ClanLib. This library exposes a generic API to read game controllers. Under the Windows version of the library, the generic API calls DirectInput. Under the Linux version of the library, the generic API calls the Linux joystick interface. Or under the Mac OS X version of the library, the generic API calls the HID Manager.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Oct 29, 2008 10:20 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
